translated: Brinck, Erik Gustaf, engineer, construction manager, Karlskrona, b. March 31, 1891 in Östersund to district chief Carl B. and Hilma Wisselkvist. Married to Gunhild Bågenholm in 1922. Children: Margareta b. 1923, Carl-Erik b. 1926. - Studied in Luleå and graduated from the Royal Institute of Technology (V) in 1913. Traveled to Belgium, Denmark, England, Finland, Italy, Norway, Switzerland, and Germany. Worked at Stockholm's city building office from 1913-1916, at Örebro's city building office from 1916-1931, and was a city engineer, construction manager, surveyor, and real estate registrar in Söderhamn from 1931-1935. He was the building manager for Karlskrona city from 1935. He was the vice chairman of the Örebro engineering club from 1928-1929, chairman of the board for Söderhamn's apprenticeship and vocational school from 1932-1934, and chairman of the board for the Technical Society in Karlskrona from 1938-1939. He has written several papers on technical subjects and enjoys sportfishing as a hobby.
